We see you, Warrior.⁠
⁠
Getting up countless times in the night. Washing and drying your third load of clothes for the day. Tying your unwashed hair into a bun. Napping when you can. Crying. Smiling at their first smile. Staring into their eyes and feeling pure joy. Showering, finally. Drinking a cold cup of coffee. Trying to make it out of the house, without falling to pieces. Feeling isolated and overwhelmed. Stepping into the fresh air to take deep breaths when you can.⁠
⁠
We are here to remind you that you’re doing your best and that you are a Warrior.⁠
⁠
📷 @laurenanddouglas.birth

This is an exciting time in the evolution of Cake Maternity, as we share our new brand campaign with you. Our purpose is to make a positive difference in women’s lives and we aim to do that by providing a space where they feel free to be their true selves.⁠
⁠
Our new brand campaign titled, we see you, Warrior, pays homage to mamas everywhere. No matter what their story looks like, we want to remind mums that they are doing their best, which is incredible.

Introducing 'Raw Motherhood Movement', it’s time to embrace what motherhood REALLY looks like.⁠

*Trigger Warning*⁠
⁠
We see you, growing the gift of life. Overcome by emotional ebbs and flows and hormonal waves. Feeling exhausted, overwhelmed and defeated, yet elated and grateful all at the same time. Living through nausea and vomiting, high risk or the fear of the fragility of life. Experiencing and accepting change in your body from painful, heavy breasts, to a growing tummy and swelling all over. The joy of hearing your baby’s heartbeat and the devastation of silence. Embracing the unknown of your baby’s birth and what you’ll be like as a mama.⁠
⁠
We are here to remind you that you’re doing your best and that you are a Warrior.⁠
⁠
📷 @laurenanddouglas.birth

OVER $250 WORTH OF PRIZES TO BE WON!⁠
⁠
As mothers ourselves, we’re tired of our Instagram feeds being filled with perfectly curated depictions of motherhood which don’t reflect our own experiences. Becoming a mum is one of the most transformative periods of our lives, but it can also leave us feeling vulnerable and subject to comparison and self doubt. It’s time we lift the veil on what it really means to be a mum, to remind us all that what we see on our feeds is not always reality. In order to do this, we need your help!⁠
⁠
JOIN THE MOVEMENT:⁠
To participate, all you have to do is answer the below questions in a feed post or Reel. Your answers can be typed out in the caption or shared as a voiceover, the choice is yours! Make sure you tag @cakematernity and use the hashtag #RawMotherhoodMovement so that we see your post.⁠
⁠
QUESTIONS:⁠
1. Tell us about a time in your motherhood journey that stands out and why?⁠
2. What do you wish you knew then that you know now?⁠
3. What would you tell yourself if you could go back in time to this moment?⁠
⁠
PRIZE:⁠
As a thank you for your time, everyone who posts prior to the 27th of January will go in the draw to win the below:⁠
Night & Day Nursing Pads (Valued at $33.90 AUD)⁠
Milk Bamboo Sleep Bra (Valued at $59.90 AUD)⁠
Cotton Candy Nursing Bra (Valued at $59.90 AUD)⁠
Honey Seamless Pregnancy Legging (Valued at $34.90 AUD)⁠
Bare Mum Postpartum Briefs (Valued at $38.90 AUD)⁠
Bare Mum Sitz Bath Salts (Valued at $32.90 AUD)⁠
⁠
T&Cs:⁠
By sharing you’re consenting to Cake Maternity sharing your post on their own social channels. Entries close 27th January at 8:59am AEST. This giveaway is in no way sponsored, endorsed or administered by, or associated with Instagram.⁠
⁠
📷 @laurenanddouglas.birth

We see you mama. Loving your kids unconditionally. Giving everything you have to tirelessly and thanklessly feed, nurture, nourish and protect them. Carrying the unseen mental load of worry and to-do lists. Feeling lost and learning to embrace change and your new normal. Grieving for your pre-kid years. Feeling the greatest love of your life, sense of purpose and connection, stronger than no other in this world. Yet, at times, feeling as equally frustrated and tested. Being burnt out, exhausted and constantly looking to achieve the elusive ‘balance’ between work and life.⁠
⁠
We are here to remind you that you’re doing your best and that you are a Warrior.⁠
⁠
📷 @laurenanddouglas.birth

Meet our Night & Day Nursing Pads⁠
⁠
Easy to wash and extremely durable, these reusable bamboo microfibre nursing pads are a sustainable choice, for the environment and your wallet.
That stare ♥️
We see you, mama. You’re sick and tired of seeing picture perfect representations of motherhood that don’t reflect your experiences.

We see you, feeding and nurturing your bub. Managing cracked nipples, mastitis, under supply, over supply, engorgement, blockages, leaking, tenderness, attachment trouble, tongue tie, pumping and the ‘Let Down’ blues. Feeling overwhelmed and struggling to attach their bub and enjoy. To those who experience pure elation and a sense of pride and calm. Navigating a new world of maternity bras and clothes and the easiest way to feed in them. To those who comp feed or decide to use bottles. A cycle of utter exhaustion when feeding to sleep is both comforting and tiring.⁠
⁠
We are here to remind you that you’re doing your best and that you are a Warrior.⁠
⁠
📷 @laurenanddouglas.birth⁠

We all know that during the early stages of pregnancy and immediately post birth, our breasts fluctuate (ahem, increase) in size.⁠
⁠
On average, women will experience growth of about 3 cup sizes, and sometimes even more when your milk comes in. I increased 5 cup sizes and (oh my) was not prepared.⁠
⁠
This increase can be especially difficult if you are already fuller busted. Not only will you be fuller but heavier too. Did you know that a breastfeeding breast is heavier than one that isn’t breastfeeding, even at the same size?! That’s why it’s so important to find the right fit and help ensure optimal breast health.
